data.description: Don’t miss this updated, 4 Bedroom, stone front colonial home with an in-ground pool, finished basement and garage. This center hall, colonial style, single-family home has been lovingly maintained with great attention to detail.  When you enter this home, you are greeted by a relaxing, heated, four season Porch/Sunroom with large windows on three sides where you can enjoy your morning coffee. You then proceed to the main living area with beautiful hardwood floors that flow throughout the entire first floor. You will first notice a beautiful Living Room where you can entertain guests as you sit around an amazing gas fireplace surrounded by built-in shelving. You will then notice the spacious formal dining room with sunlight coming through the bay window.  You will love the updated (2022) gourmet kitchen which has been equipped with Thermador and Bosch stainless steel appliances, recessed lighting. gas cooking, a large farmhouse sink, stylish backsplash, and lots of upgraded cabinets with soft-close features and pull-out drawers.  The highlight of this home is the lighted garden oasis in the back yard which has a heated in-ground pool with new liner and pool equipment which is protected by a new 6 foot privacy fence.  The backyard also has a secured 12x10 foot gazebo for outdoor dining, seating areas throughout the yard, mature trees, and perennial flowers in the gardens.  Upstairs is the master suite with a walk-in closet which contains built in custom closet system and bath.  There are three additional bedrooms and a hall bath. The 4th bedroom is currently being used as a gigantic, walk-in closet but can also be used as an office or nursery. As if this is not enough, the lower level has been partially finished with a large entertainment and play area which extends the livability of this move-in ready home. You will find in the accompanying documents a long list of upgrades which have been implemented recently including a high-efficiency furnace, pool equipment and liner, and luxury flooring.  The location of this home is hard to beat. Williams Park is just 300 yards away and the elementary, middle, and high schools as well as the library and public transportation are all just an easy walk away. The restaurants, grocery stores and shops of Springfield are all within a 1 or 2-mile drive.  Springfield is also close to Philadelphia International airport and many well-known, major shopping areas and recreation areas.
